# Elombe Workflow Standards

Before editing, state:
- issue/feature being solved
- likely affected files
- change type using commit-aligned categories (\fix`, `feat`, `refactor`, `style`, `docs`, `chore`, `test`, `perf`)

For each new task, recommend:
1) branch name
2) implementation plan
3) likely affected files
4) testing checklist
5) commit message suggestion

Branch format:
- elombe/<issue-number-or-task>-<short-description>
- fallback: elombe/task-<short-description>

Keep changes single-purpose and small.
Avoid direct work on main except explicit emergency hotfix.

Before commit, remind to review:
- git status
- git diff
- changed files
- secrets/API keys
- unwanted files
- debug logs
- broken links
- formatting

Commit format:
- type(scope): short description
- types: feat, fix, refactor, style, docs, chore, test, perf

When asked for PR description, use:
- ## Summary
- ## Changes Made
- ## Testing
- ## Screenshots / Notes
- ## Risk Level
- ## Rollback Plan
